cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.CL, cs.CR 

The paper combines social structure and content analysis to study opinion evolution dynamics in Egypt during the summer of 2013 on Twitter. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). However, given the focus on social networks and opinion dynamics, cs.SI and cs.SD are the most likely categories.
